\centerline{\Huge\bf PCB-RELEASE command reference
{\scriptsize \copyright 1996, Thomas Nau}}
\bigskip
\small

\hfill
\begin{minipage}[t]{\BoxWidth}
\renewcommand{\thefootnote}{\arabic{footnote}}
\fbox{\rule[\BoxRaise]{0cm}{\BoxHeight} \begin{tabular}[t]{ll}
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf misc operations} \\
backspace & remove object \\
\Shift\Ctrl\Btn1 & remove object \\
escape & reset mode \\
\Btn1 & create object or part \\
space & create object or part \\
u & undo operation \\
tab & switch viewing side \\
\Shift\Ctrl u & clear undo-list \\
cursor key & move crosshair \\
\Shift cursor key & move crosshair 10 times \\
q & change square flag \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf connections} \\
\Shift c & reset connections \\
f & find LPPV \footnote{LPPV: line, pin, polygon or via} connection \\
\Shift backspace & remove LPPV connection \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf user (:) commands} \\
:l [file] & load data file \\
:le [file] & load element to buffer \\
:m [file] & load layout to buffer \\
:q & quit application \\
:s [file] & save data as file \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf display} \\
c & center display \\
g & increment grid \\
\Shift g & decrement grid \\
r & clear and redraw output \\
z & enlarge output \\
\Shift z & shrink output \\
drag \Shift\Mod\Btn3 & select objects in box \\
\end{tabular}}
\end{minipage}
%
%
%
\hfill
\begin{minipage}[t]{\BoxWidth}
\fbox{\rule[\BoxRaise]{0cm}{\BoxHeight} \begin{tabular}[t]{ll}
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf selection} \\
\Btn3 & toggle object selection \\
drag \Mod\Btn3 & select objects in rectangle \\
\Shift m & move selected to current layer \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf copy and move} \\
drag \Btn2 & move object \\
drag \Mod\Btn2 & copy object \\
drag \Shift\Mod\Btn2 & rubberband move \\
m & move to current layer \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf element} \\
d & display pinout \\
\Shift d & open pinout window \\
n & change name \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf via} \\
\Fun1 & enter via-mode \\
n & change name \\
s & increment size \\
\Shift s & decrement size \\
\Mod s & increment drilling hole \\
\Shift\Mod s & decrement drilling hole \\
v & increment initial size \\
\Shift v & decrement initial size \\
\Mod v & inc. initial drilling hole \\
\Shift\Mod v & dec. initial drilling hole \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf line} \\
\Fun2 & enter line mode \\
l & increment initial size \\
\Shift l & decrement initial size \\
s & increment size \\
\Shift s & decrement size \\
\end{tabular}}
\end{minipage}
%
%
%
\hfill
\begin{minipage}[t]{\BoxWidth}
\fbox{\rule[\BoxRaise]{0cm}{\BoxHeight} \begin{tabular}[t]{ll}
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf pastebuffer} \\
\Fun3 & enter pastebuffer-mode \\
\Shift \Fun3 & rotate 90 degree cc \\
\Btn1 & copy to layout \\
space & copy to layout \\
\Shift 1$\cdots$5 & select buffer \# 1$\cdots$5 \\
x & copy selected objects to buffer \\
\Shift x & cut selected objects to buffer \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf polygon} \\
\Fun4 & enter rectangle-mode \\
\Fun6 & enter polygon-mode \\
p & go to previous corner \\
\Shift p & close path \\
insert & insert a corner \\
\Shift\Ctrl insert & remove a corner \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf text} \\
\Fun5 & enter text-mode \\
n & edit string \\
s & increment size \\
\Shift s & decrement size \\
t & increment initial size \\
\Shift t & decrement initial size \\
 & \\
\multicolumn{2}{c}{\bf pin} \\
n & change name \\
s & increment size \\
\Shift s & decrement size \\
\Mod s & increment drilling hole \\
\Shift\Mod s & decrement drilling hole \\
\end{tabular}}
\end{minipage}
\hfill

\medskip
Obviously \Shift, \Ctrl, \Mod, \Fun \space and \Btn \space mean the shift,
control, modifier1 (BTNMOD for buttons), function key and mouse button.

